  <h1>
   gesture_get_drag_distance
  </h1>
  This function is used to get the distance it takes for a
  <a href="../../../../The_Asset_Editors/Object_Properties/Gesture_Events.htm">
   Dragging Gesture
  </a>
  event to be triggered by the movement of a touch or click. The distance is measured in inches and has a default value of 0.1.
  <h4>
   <b>
    Syntax:
   </b>
  </h4>
  <pre><code class="language-gml">gesture_get_drag_distance();
</code></pre>
  <h4>
   Returns:
  </h4>
  <pre><code class="language-gml"><a href="../../../../../GameMaker_Language/GML_Overview/Data_Types.htm">
 Real
</a>
(inches)
</code></pre>
  <h4>
   Example:
  </h4>
  <pre><code class="language-gml">if gesture_get_drag_distance() != 0.1
{
    gesture_drag_distance(0.1);
}
</code></pre>
  The above code checks to see if the drag distance for gestures is set to 0.1 inches and if it is not it sets it to that value.
 </body>
</html>